"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-06-olympian-sent-home-not-allowed-compete-boyfriend-21370158\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"An athlete has been axed from theParisOlympicsafter publicly complaining about being dropped fromGermany's relay team and missing the chance to race alongside her boyfriend.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 173, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Luna Bulmahn was surprisingly snubbed for the 4x400m mixed relay, a decision she and her partner Jean Paul Bredau angrily reacted to.\", \"from\": 175, \"to\": 308, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 175, \"end\": 187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luna_Bulmahn\", \"score\": 0.9999955507072473, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Luna Bulmahn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luna_Bulmahn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luna_Bulmahn\"}, {\"begin\": 272, \"end\": 281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_Paul\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jean Paul\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_Paul\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_Paul\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Yes, I am the second fastest 400-meter athlete on paper,' Bulmahn wrote onInstagram.\", \"from\": 310, \"to\": 395, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'No, I was not nominated for the mixed relay.'\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 443, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bulmahn's place was taken by Alica Schmidt but Germany performed awfully in the event, finishing seventh in their round one race.\", \"from\": 445, \"to\": 574, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 474, \"end\": 487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alica_Schmidt\", \"score\": 0.9999999993119673, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alica Schmidt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alica_Schmidt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alica_Schmidt\"}, {\"begin\": 492, \"end\": 499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6792036756278813, \"rank\": 0.391537466881696, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB went onto win bronze in the final.\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 617, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the Paris 2024 Olympics  After the race, a frustrated Bredau suggested his girlfriend's absence affected their performance, saying: 'Not everything went perfectly beforehand.\", \"from\": 619, \"to\": 841, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's why I did not have the energy.\", \"from\": 842, \"to\": 879, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'A few decisions were made that not everyone approved.\", \"from\": 881, \"to\": 935, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The DLV (Germany's Athletics Association) made it very clear: the fastest four should run.\", \"from\": 936, \"to\": 1026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 940, \"end\": 943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Domain_Name_System_Security_Extensions\", \"score\": 0.9949231545134263, \"rank\": 0.0051027513667395675, \"text\": \"DLV\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Domain_Name_System_Security_Extensions\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Domain_Name_System_Security_Extensions\"}, {\"begin\": 945, \"end\": 952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6792036756278813, \"rank\": 0.391537466881696, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A different decision was made.'\", \"from\": 1027, \"to\": 1058, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bredau late apologised for his remarks and was cleared to continue racing in Paris but the DLV were not so lenient with Bulmahn, dropping her from the women's 4x400m relay as punishment.\", \"from\": 1060, \"to\": 1246, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1137, \"end\": 1142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999922693, \"rank\": 7.825715867248272e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1151, \"end\": 1154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Domain_Name_System_Security_Extensions\", \"score\": 0.9949231545134263, \"rank\": 0.0051027513667395675, \"text\": \"DLV\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Domain_Name_System_Security_Extensions\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Domain_Name_System_Security_Extensions\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reports also say she has been sent home from the games.\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1303, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A statement from the DLV on the matter read: 'The line-up was made with a view to a successful mixed relay team.\", \"from\": 1305, \"to\": 1417, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1326, \"end\": 1329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Domain_Name_System_Security_Extensions\", \"score\": 0.9949231545134263, \"rank\": 0.0051027513667395675, \"text\": \"DLV\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Domain_Name_System_Security_Extensions\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Domain_Name_System_Security_Extensions\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The decision was made unanimously by the DLV coaching team and was explained to the athletes.\", \"from\": 1418, \"to\": 1511, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1459, \"end\": 1462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Domain_Name_System_Security_Extensions\", \"score\": 0.9949231545134263, \"rank\": 